      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) is a purist-spec example of high-revving, naturally aspirated engineering. Powered by the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six, it features individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure Double VANOS system, delivering a visceral 8,000 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a crisp Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and the factory M Variable Differential Lock for superior corner-exit traction. This chassis has been proactively maintained with documented subframe reinforcement and a recent valve clearance adjustment. While the exterior shows honest signs of use, the mechanical components are dialed in, featuring a refreshed cooling system and bushings to preserve the communicative steering and 50/50 weight distribution that defines this platform.",
